data.title: Xpert I #5 by Amrit Rai, Gary Millward, & Robert Wood (Editors): Very Good Soft cover 1st Edition
data.meta_description: 1st Edition - Soft cover - Condition: Very Good - London: Xpert I, 1979. Staple-bound softcover. 30 pages including covers. Very good. Minor edgewear and creasing at corners. Some minor pulling to staples, though still tight. Bottom of page 10, written in marker and pen: "You have won Protex single, save this copy. Ring 22675 and ask for Rob. Evenings please." Nice copy of scarce 1979 London punk zine. Featuring interviews with The Police, The Members, Arturo Bassick of The Lurkers / Pinpoint, Howard Wall & Esso of The Lurkers + writing on the U.K. Subs, The Stranglers, The Fall, Patrick Fitzgerald, The Ramones, Corridor, Raincoats, Medium Medium, Essential Logic, Mekons, The Damned, The Knack and record reviews, etc. - Xpert I #5
data.text:
About this Item

London: Xpert I, 1979. Staple-bound softcover. 30 pages including covers. Very good. Minor edgewear and creasing at corners. Some minor pulling to staples, though still tight. Bottom of page 10, written in marker and pen: "You have won Protex single, save this copy. Ring 22675 and ask for Rob. Evenings please." Nice copy of scarce 1979 London punk zine. Featuring interviews with The Police, The Members, Arturo Bassick of The Lurkers / Pinpoint, Howard Wall & Esso of The Lurkers + writing on the U.K. Subs, The Stranglers, The Fall, Patrick Fitzgerald, The Ramones, Corridor, Raincoats, Medium Medium, Essential Logic, Mekons, The Damned, The Knack and record reviews, etc. Seller Inventory # ABE-1722285433113
